article.headline: W. Carolina 73, Binghamton 44
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Mike Williams scored 15 points to lead Western Carolina to a 73-44 victory over Binghamton on Tuesday night. The Catamounts (3-1) dominated the first half, rolling to a 33-13 halftime score. They were 16-for-26 from the field (61.5 percent) and held Binghamton (1-4) to only three first-half field goals in the O'Reilly Auto Parts Classic. It was the Bearcats' fourth straight loss. Western Carolina took a 20-6 advantage on Kendall Russell's jumper with 7:23 remaining. After Binghamton's Kyrie Sutton scored on a jumper to cut the lead to 20-8, Williams hit a layup for a 22-8 advantage with 6:22 left in the first half. The Catamounts scored the next seven points for a 29-8 lead with 1:52 left. Harouna Mutombo added 11 points and Jake Robinson scored 10 points for the Catamounts. Greer Wright led Binghamton with 21 points and Dylan Talley added 11 points.
